Summary: Discusses the performance implications of different scripting languages in Godot.
Languages
Godot supports a number of different languages, and it is worth bearing in mind that there are trade-offs involved. Some languages are designed for ease of use at the cost of speed, and others are faster but more difficult to work with.

Built-in engine functions run at the same speed regardless of the scripting language you choose. If your project is making a lot of calculations in its own code, consider moving those calculations to a faster language.
---CHUNK---
Document: CPU Optimization
Path: godot/tutorials/performance/cpu_optimization.rst
Summary: This section discusses the performance implications of using GDScript and C# for CPU-intensive tasks in Godot.
GDScript is designed for ease of use and rapid iteration, prioritizing simplicity over raw performance. For computationally heavy tasks, consider using other languages.
C# offers a good balance between performance and ease of use and has first-class support in Godot. However, be mindful of potential garbage collection pauses and memory leaks during gameplay. Object pooling is a common technique to mitigate garbage collection issues, though it is not covered in this guide.
---CHUNK---
